main event: A bright white object was observed in the sky over Seattle, Washington on 9 June 1963.
interesting points: The object was stationary and estimated to be traveling at 15,000 mph, much brighter than a star,The sighting lasted for about 15 minutes,Three confirmed witnesses used binoculars to observe the object,The object showed no color changes, blinking lights, or sound during the observation,Similar reports from others in the area noted it moving slower than Sputnik.
sighted object: one bright white object in the sky
witness description: Mr. Business and 4 other persons observing from the area
